Used to be my Starbucks of choice. Fairly friendly Baristas, usually lots of seating, and separate male and female keypad secured bathrooms (altho 1-stall). Some of the Baristas can be a little snarky, but that's just the way they are there.  The bar seating is cute. Cleanliness is a bit of an issue. Consistent on the preparation.  However, since the installation of the SALT parking gate, it can be really difficult to get out of the parking lot because there is only one unattended line and for some reason many people have a hard time figuring out how the automated gate works. It's 1 hour of free parking, but it really ends up being much less,  because you will need to leave early... if you get stuck in this line you will end up having to pay.  Automated gate system also does not always work. Several times was in and out in under 10 minutes but the automated gate refused to open unless I paid $3 (credit card only, natch). I usually just pay it because it's too much hassle--the only human assistance is in the SALT parking office is on the other side of the building, it takes time since they aren't always in the little booth, and there is no way to back up & park in the stall to avoid paying before you talk to them because there are always people behind you in line. Being held hostage like that is still NOT ok, so last time it happened, finally took time out, parked and went around the corner to the SALT parking office, where the young man on duty said he would process a refund for me but it would take 6 to 8 weeks. Needless to say, I never received the refund.  If you park on on-street and are paying for parking, or work at one of the nearby businesses and walk there, then I guess it's an okay location. There is still a homeless problem, or some really natural smelling Bohemian types that live in the area? Be prepared to have a sensory experience. But the parking hassle is the deal-breaker. I'd rather go to the location by The Ward Theaters, or the location at Ward and Auahi. Free parking at either of those, and very close by.
